<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 7:49PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Marion
County through 845 PM CDT...
At 749 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tremont, or 12 miles south of Red Bay, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Weston, Byrd, Bexar, Pigeye, Shottsville, Rankin Fite
Airport and Marion County Public Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
